---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NavLinkShowcase from '../components/NavLinkShowcase.astro';
---

<Layout title="Destinations" description="Explore Bali's sacred regions - Ubud, North Bali, East Bali, and West Bali. Each landscape holds its own energy and invitation.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative h-[70vh] flex items-center justify-center bg-stone-900 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-linear-to-b from-stone-900/60 via-stone-900/40 to-stone-900/80 z-10"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500375592092-40eb2168fd21?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1920&q=80&ixlib=rb-4.0.3')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
    
    <div class="relative z-20 text-center px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="hero-animate text-gold-500 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-6">Sacred Landscapes</p>
      <h1 class="hero-animate hero-animate-delay-1 font-serif text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl text-stone-50 leading-tight">
        Where Will Your<br/>Soul Wander?
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <div class="prose-luxury reveal">
        <p>
          Bali is not one island—it is many worlds contained within sacred shores. 
          Each region breathes with its own rhythm, holds its own mysteries, and 
          offers its own path to awakening. The journey you seek may call you to 
          the artistic heart of Ubud, the untouched north, the ancient east, or 
          the wild west. Perhaps it calls you to all.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Ubud -->
  <section id="ubud" class="section-padding bg-stone-100">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div class="relative h-150 order-2 lg:order-1 reveal-scale image-reveal">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/nature/rice-terrace.webp')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -right-6 w-48 h-48 bg-[url('/images/culture/offerings.webp')] bg-cover bg-center border-4 border-stone-50 hidden lg:block"></div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2 reveal">
          <p class="text-gold-600 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">The Heart</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-900 mb-6">Ubud</h2>
          <div class="divider mb-8"></div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="text-lg italic text-stone-700">
              Where rice terraces cascade like stairways to heaven and every stone 
              holds the memory of a thousand prayers.
            </p>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">The Atmosphere</h3>
              <p>
                Ubud pulses with creative energy tempered by deep stillness. Morning 
                mist rises from the Ayung River as artisans begin their daily devotions. 
                Galleries and temples stand side by side, each honoring beauty in its 
                own way. Here, the boundary between art and spirituality dissolves.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Spiritual & Cultural Energy</h3>
              <p>
                This is where Bali's artistic soul resides. Master painters, woodcarvers, 
                and silversmiths continue traditions passed through generations. Sacred 
                dance performances unfold in temple courtyards. Healers and priests offer 
                guidance to those who seek. The veil between worlds is thin here.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Adventure Element</h3>
              <p>
                Trek through ancient rice terraces at dawn. Cycle through hidden villages 
                where time moves differently. Discover waterfalls that few have witnessed. 
                The adventure here is intimate—a journey inward as much as outward.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Emotional Benefit</h3>
              <p>
                Ubud offers the gift of creative awakening. Here, you remember what it 
                means to create, to feel, to be moved by beauty. You leave with your 
                senses sharpened and your spirit renewed.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- North Bali -->
  <section id="north-bali" class="section-padding bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-gold-600 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">The Untouched</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-900 mb-6">North Bali</h2>
          <div class="divider mb-8"></div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="text-lg italic text-stone-700">
              Where volcanic peaks pierce the clouds and black sand beaches meet 
              waters that have known only the footsteps of fishermen.
            </p>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">The Atmosphere</h3>
              <p>
                The north remains Bali's secret—a landscape of dramatic contrasts where 
                mountains plunge toward a calmer sea. Villages here move to older rhythms. 
                The air is cooler, the pace slower, the connection to the land more 
                immediate. This is Bali before the world discovered it.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Spiritual & Cultural Energy</h3>
              <p>
                Ancient temples cling to cliffsides, their ceremonies witnessed only by 
                the devoted. Hot springs emerge from volcanic earth, carrying minerals 
                and memories of the island's fiery birth. Buddhist monasteries offer 
                silent refuge. The spiritual energy here is raw and unmediated.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Adventure Element</h3>
              <p>
                Summit Mount Batur before dawn to witness the sun rise over the caldera. 
                Dive pristine reefs untouched by crowds. Trek through coffee plantations 
                and spice gardens. Discover twin lakes cradled in volcanic craters. 
                Adventure here rewards those who venture beyond the familiar.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Emotional Benefit</h3>
              <p>
                North Bali offers the gift of solitude and perspective. Standing where 
                few stand, seeing what few see, you reconnect with the wild part of 
                yourself that modern life has quieted.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="relative h-150">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/nature/banyumala-waterfall.webp')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -left-6 w-48 h-48 bg-[url('/images/nature/jungle-waterfall.webp')] bg-cover bg-center border-4 border-stone-50 hidden lg:block"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- East Bali -->
  <section id="east-bali" class="section-padding bg-stone-100">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div class="relative h-150 order-2 lg:order-1">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/temples/gunung-kawi.webp')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -right-6 w-48 h-48 bg-[url('/images/culture/tirta-gangga.webp')] bg-cover bg-center border-4 border-stone-50 hidden lg:block"></div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
          <p class="text-gold-600 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">The Ancient</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-900 mb-6">East Bali</h2>
          <div class="divider mb-8"></div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="text-lg italic text-stone-700">
              Where the mother temple watches over all and sacred waters have 
              purified pilgrims for a thousand years.
            </p>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">The Atmosphere</h3>
              <p>
                East Bali carries the weight of history and the lightness of devotion. 
                Mount Agung, the island's highest peak and most sacred mountain, dominates 
                the horizon. Ancient kingdoms left their mark in water palaces and royal 
                temples. The energy here is regal, reverent, and deeply rooted.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Spiritual & Cultural Energy</h3>
              <p>
                Besakih, the mother temple, crowns the slopes of Mount Agung—the spiritual 
                axis of Balinese Hinduism. Tirta Gangga's sacred springs offer purification 
                rituals unchanged for centuries. Traditional villages preserve customs that 
                predate memory. This is where Bali's spiritual heart beats strongest.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Adventure Element</h3>
              <p>
                Trek the slopes of Mount Agung for those called to the summit. Snorkel 
                the famous waters of Amed and Tulamben, where a shipwreck has become a 
                coral garden. Explore salt-making villages where ancient techniques 
                continue. The adventure here connects you to elemental forces.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Emotional Benefit</h3>
              <p>
                East Bali offers the gift of reverence. In the presence of the sacred 
                mountain and ancient temples, ego quiets and something deeper awakens. 
                You leave humbled and elevated in equal measure.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- South Bali -->
  <section id="south-bali" class="section-padding bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-gold-600 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">The Vibrant</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-900 mb-6">South Bali</h2>
          <div class="divider mb-8"></div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="text-lg italic text-stone-700">
              Where dramatic clifftop temples meet world-renowned beaches and 
              the pulse of contemporary Bali beats strongest.
            </p>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">The Atmosphere</h3>
              <p>
                South Bali is where tradition and modernity dance together. From the 
                sacred Uluwatu Temple perched on dramatic limestone cliffs to the 
                sophisticated beach clubs of Seminyak, this region offers the full 
                spectrum of Balinese experience. The energy here is dynamic, cosmopolitan, 
                yet still deeply rooted in island spirituality.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Spiritual & Cultural Energy</h3>
              <p>
                Uluwatu Temple stands as a guardian of the island's southwestern tip, 
                where Kecak fire dances unfold against sunset skies. The Bukit Peninsula 
                holds hidden temples and sacred caves. Even amid the sophistication, 
                daily offerings line every doorstep and ceremony processions pause traffic 
                with beautiful regularity.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Adventure Element</h3>
              <p>
                Surf legendary breaks at Padang Padang and Bingin. Discover hidden 
                beaches accessible only by steep cliff stairs. Experience world-class 
                dining and nightlife. Explore the artistic enclaves of Canggu. The 
                adventure here blends adrenaline with sophistication.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Emotional Benefit</h3>
              <p>
                South Bali offers the gift of vibrant living. Here, you experience 
                Bali's ability to hold both the sacred and the celebratory, the 
                ancient and the contemporary. You leave feeling fully alive and 
                deeply connected to the island's dynamic spirit.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="relative h-150">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/beach/uluwatu-beach.webp')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -left-6 w-48 h-48 bg-[url('/images/beach/coastal-view.webp')] bg-cover bg-center border-4 border-stone-50 hidden lg:block"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- West Bali -->
  <section id="west-bali" class="section-padding bg-stone-100">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-gold-600 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">The Wild</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-900 mb-6">West Bali</h2>
          <div class="divider mb-8"></div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="text-lg italic text-stone-700">
              Where national parks protect the last wild frontiers and sunset 
              temples stand as gateways between worlds.
            </p>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">The Atmosphere</h3>
              <p>
                West Bali is the island's untamed edge—a realm of protected forests, 
                hidden beaches, and communities that live close to the land. The pace 
                here is dictated by nature: the tides, the seasons, the flight patterns 
                of rare birds. This is Bali at its most elemental.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Spiritual & Cultural Energy</h3>
              <p>
                Tanah Lot rises from the sea, one of Bali's most sacred temples, 
                accessible only when the tides permit. The Jatiluwih rice terraces, 
                a UNESCO World Heritage site, demonstrate the ancient subak irrigation 
                system—a living philosophy of harmony between humans and nature.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Adventure Element</h3>
              <p>
                Trek through West Bali National Park in search of the endangered Bali 
                starling. Surf world-class breaks known only to the devoted. Discover 
                secret beaches accessible only by boat. Cycle through UNESCO-protected 
                rice terraces. The adventure here is wild and unscripted.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Emotional Benefit</h3>
              <p>
                West Bali offers the gift of wildness. Here, you remember that you 
                are part of something vast and untamed. The boundaries of the 
                controlled life dissolve, and freedom becomes tangible.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="relative h-150 order-2 lg:order-1">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/nature/nature-scene.webp')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -right-6 w-48 h-48 bg-[url('/images/nature/river-path.webp')] bg-cover bg-center border-4 border-stone-50 hidden lg:block"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Nusa Penida -->
  <section id="nusa-penida" class="section-padding bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-gold-600 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">The Dramatic</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-900 mb-6">Nusa Penida</h2>
          <div class="divider mb-8"></div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="text-lg italic text-stone-700">
              Where towering sea cliffs plunge into crystal waters and nature 
              remains gloriously untamed and awe-inspiring.
            </p>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">The Atmosphere</h3>
              <p>
                Nusa Penida is Bali's wild sister island—a rugged paradise where 
                dramatic limestone cliffs meet pristine turquoise waters. The landscape 
                here is raw and powerful, shaped by the relentless ocean. Roads wind 
                through untouched terrain, revealing viewpoints that steal your breath 
                and remind you of nature's magnificent scale.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Spiritual & Cultural Energy</h3>
              <p>
                The island holds deep spiritual significance for the Balinese, considered 
                a place of purification and pilgrimage. Ancient temples perch on clifftops, 
                their ceremonies witnessed by few. The local communities maintain traditions 
                largely unchanged by tourism, offering glimpses into authentic island life.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Adventure Element</h3>
              <p>
                Swim with majestic manta rays at Manta Point. Trek to the iconic 
                Kelingking Beach—the famous T-Rex cliff. Snorkel crystal-clear waters 
                at Crystal Bay. Discover the natural infinity pool of Angel's Billabong. 
                Every corner of this island rewards the adventurous spirit.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Emotional Benefit</h3>
              <p>
                Nusa Penida offers the gift of wonder. Standing before its dramatic 
                landscapes, you feel small in the best possible way—connected to 
                something vast and timeless. You leave with a renewed sense of 
                adventure and appreciation for nature's artistry.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="relative h-150">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/beach/rocky-coast.webp')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -left-6 w-48 h-48 bg-[url('/images/nature/nature-02.webp')] bg-cover bg-center border-4 border-stone-50 hidden lg:block"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Nusa Lembongan -->
  <section id="nusa-lembongan" class="section-padding bg-stone-100">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div class="relative h-150 order-2 lg:order-1">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/beach/beach-panorama.webp')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -right-6 w-48 h-48 bg-[url('/images/beach/beach-02.webp')] bg-cover bg-center border-4 border-stone-50 hidden lg:block"></div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
          <p class="text-gold-600 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">The Serene</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-900 mb-6">Nusa Lembongan</h2>
          <div class="divider mb-8"></div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="text-lg italic text-stone-700">
              Where time slows to island pace, seaweed farmers tend turquoise 
              shallows, and barefoot luxury meets authentic village charm.
            </p>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">The Atmosphere</h3>
              <p>
                Nusa Lembongan is the gentle counterpart to Penida's drama—a small 
                island paradise where scooters outnumber cars and the rhythm of life 
                follows the tides. Sandy lanes wind past traditional seaweed farms, 
                boutique resorts, and clifftop cafes. The atmosphere is relaxed, 
                intimate, and genuinely welcoming.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Spiritual & Cultural Energy</h3>
              <p>
                Despite its small size, the island maintains strong spiritual traditions. 
                Temple ceremonies punctuate the calendar, and the yellow bridge connecting 
                to neighboring Nusa Ceningan has become a symbol of island connection. 
                The seaweed farming culture represents a sustainable harmony with the sea.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Adventure Element</h3>
              <p>
                Surf the legendary breaks of Playgrounds and Lacerations. Kayak through 
                mangrove forests at sunrise. Snorkel vibrant coral gardens. Cross the 
                iconic yellow bridge to explore Nusa Ceningan's hidden beaches. Watch 
                the sunset from Devil's Tear as waves explode against the rocks.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-stone-900 mb-2">Emotional Benefit</h3>
              <p>
                Nusa Lembongan offers the gift of simplicity. Here, the complications 
                of modern life fade away, replaced by the simple pleasures of sun, 
                sea, and genuine human connection. You leave feeling restored and 
                reminded of what truly matters.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <NavLinkShowcase heading="Journey Through Our Core Pages" theme="light" />

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="relative py-32 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/temples/temple-gate.webp')] bg-cover bg-center bg-fixed"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-stone-900/70"></div>
    
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center px-6">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-stone-50 mb-8">
        Which Landscape Calls to You?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-stone-300 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
        Let us help you discover where your journey begins—and where it might lead.
      </p>
      <a href="/begin" class="btn-luxury-outline">Begin the Conversation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
